node.text:
Can you believe this was 5 years ago, @jimmyfallon?! American Pharoah charmed us all at the 2015 @BreedersCup… Can’t wait to watch the 2020 edition on November 6&7! I’ll miss being at @Keeneland in person, but we’ll be tuning in on NBC Sports all weekend from home.

Join me! 

Don’t miss a second of the action!
Nov 6.  NBCSN: 2:00 PM (ET)
Nov 7.  NBCSN: NOON (ET)
Nov 7.  NBC:  2:30 ET (ET)
#BreedersCup #BC20  #MyBreedersCup #TBT @NBCSports

This week we are so honored to work with the American Gold Star Mothers. They are a group comprised of families who have lost a son or daughter due to their service in the military. They provide support to each other, and also honor military members and veterans by continuing to serve.
.
These parents have been through the most unthinkable tragedy we could ever imagine by losing a child. This week, our donation to American Gold Star Mothers will allow them to create a program to provide financial assistance to their members who have been impacted by COVID-19.
.
Although nothing can compare to what they have already been through, we hope that some financial relief and support during this pandemic is able to help their families.
.
We couldn’t be more honored to work with them, especially on Mother’s Day weekend. To every Gold Star Mother, and every mother who has a child that is currently serving, or has served our Country, thank you for your incredible strength and sacrifice. #MothersDay #COVID19 #WinsForWarriors @justinverlander

New York is such a beloved city to @justinverlander and me, and as most know it has been experiencing some of the most devastating spreads of this virus. We connected with Covenant House New York, and they are overcoming extreme obstacles to continue to provide shelter, food and resources for youth experiencing homelessness.
.
Currently, at @covenanthouseny they are caring for 10 children who have tested positive, while 30 staff members are in recovery as well. Overall demand of the 24/7 needed care has drastically increased and they are doing an incredible job responding during this crisis by implementing safety precautions and new programs with a special emphasis on mental health.
.
We are so grateful to be able to donate and support their mission. Also we are extremely grateful to @bellacanvas who, for the second week in a row, has generously donated by sending 25,000 masks to Covenant House New York.
.
Also, @covenant_house is an international organization operating in 31 cities throughout six countries. Thank you sincerely to Hannah and Cal McNair (@HannahMcNair11) who have joined us and are donating to @covenanthousetx which is located in Houston.
.
We’ve included more information about Covenant House in our stories. Thank you to all who pulled together to help make an impact in both New York and Houston. Please stay safe and to all those working to help and heal our communities, thank you for all you do! #covid19 #newyork #houston #covenanthouse #bellacanvas

@justinverlander and I have been following the #COVID19 spread in Michigan and are heartbroken for Detroit, a city so close to our hearts. With such deep ties to this amazing and resilient city we wanted to focus our efforts on supporting both the community and first responders. We’ve especially seen the impact on the Detroit Police Department and reached out to learn how we could help. Together we quickly identified their areas of need and are so grateful for several collaborations and extremely generous organizations that rushed to support:
.
Through a partnership with @bellacanvas, we are sending 25,000 masks to @detroit_police to be distributed among their officers. They are also stocking each patrol car with masks and distributing them to people and communities in need.
.
@ford through @fordfund is donating face shields for every single police officer, paramedic and fire fighter in Detroit! This is such an important and extra layer of protection while helping many who are sick and needing their assistance.
.
Also, in order to help slow the spread, the Detroit Police Dept. has instituted strict safety measures such as temperature checks for all staff members. They expressed a need for touchless thermometers and through a donation to and an incredible effort by @bethennyfrankel ‘s #bstrong and @globalempowermentmission they were able to help fill that deficit.
.
Lastly, getting food safely to those on the front lines is a major initiative, and we are donating to @feedthefrontlinesdetroit. They are working with local restaurants to deliver meals to healthcare workers and first responders. This is a wonderful initiative to support both the local restaurant industry and many who are on the front lines every day. .
We’ve included more information and links to these inspiring organizations in our stories. Thank you to all who pulled together to help make an impact in #Detroit. Please stay safe and to all those working to help and heal our communities, thank you for all you do!  #staysafe #stayhome #savelives #bellacanvas #fordfund #feedthefrontlinesdetroit

node.text: @justinverlander and I are incredibly grateful for the countless organizations that are doing so much for their communities during these unprecedented times. We recently announced that we will be donating to and highlighting a new nonprofit each week, and we’re excited to shine a light on the incredible work being done at @houstonfoodbank. They are part of the @feedingamerica family and the largest food bank in the Country. We learned that they are giving over 750,000 lbs of food EACH day, to many people who are experiencing hunger for the first time. We’re so grateful for their tireless work and the ability to reach so many people who are struggling to feed their families. For those needing assistance please visit your closest Feeding America location for help. And we understand that not everyone can give during these hard times, but for those of you who can I’ve included more information in stories. We’ll be going live with Houston Food Bank this weekend so hope you tune in to see the incredible work they’re doing. Please stay safe and to all those working to serve their communities, thank you for everything you do! #COVID19 #foodisessential #foodforbetterlives #houstonfoodbank #feedingamerica
